{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"86ad1812-9229-4e14-a887-1d44b37fd0e0","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types/modules from files listed *above* them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_X8znJPSFAyHANWiBiIg1mc","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-f5d0d1b456fd4fe1a9e4e1833641989d/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-f5d0d1b456fd4fe1a9e4e1833641989d/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"395ebd21-10b7-402c-a738-7c86d05b49a6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed earlier in the project file. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` has `open BrokenOrder.Domain`, meaning it depends on `Domain.fs`. Since `Domain.fs` comes after `Services.fs` in the compile order, the compiler can't find `BrokenOrder.Domain` when compiling `Services.fs`.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n\n\n1. `Domain.fs` (no dependencies)\n2. `Services.fs` (depends on Domain)\n3. `Program.fs` (depends on Domain and Services)","outputTokens":492,"requestId":"2812:19764A:1B31ABB:1E3E332:69FA8F79"},"id":"b559d909-b62f-4ee0-80d9-c400d81fca7f","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:46:58.034Z","parentId":"968d1b40-5e72-4958-9a20-3537e4fd83d8"}
